        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> I would like to see the following looked into:</P><P>Dot Stacking - Nothing is more important to us than this.</P><P>Caster skills - I think it is time we were allowed to max out specialization on all schools of magic, not just the one.</P><P>Caster Focus Items - We were promised them and should get them. Lower mana cost, faster casting time, lower recast time, spell effect amplification. These things should be available to all casters. As haste items for melee have varying degrees of power, so should our focus items. These things should not be the exclusive domain of the more privileged who belong to stronger guilds.</P><P>More Spell slots - Verant have said that we will see no more than 8 slots ever. There must be a way to access more spells during combat. I would like the ability to use a replacement 8 spell lineup via a hotkey. Spellbank 1 and Spellbank 2. Or perhaps the ability through questing to have a spell effect transferred to an item. Could be made available to 50 or 55 plus casters and the item would have to be equipped and changed to no-drop permanently.</P><P></P><P>Abaraxas Malfoy<BR>Defiler of the Tribunal</P><P>Edited by - abaraxas on 02/28/2002  07:13:19<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
