        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> Consider this, Verant would have us believe that a young Harry Potter (lvl 1 wizard) can somehow memorize the same number of spells that a Gandalf the Wizard (lvl 60 wizard) can. This makes no sense!</P><P>Over time an experienced veteran caster *should* be able to memorize more spells.</P><P>Let's consider a lvl 1 warrior vs. a lvl 60 warrior. Naturally the 60 warrior has at his/her disposal numerous abilities and disciplines. Why can't the same be true for lvl 60 casters? Why can't we at the very least have 10, 12, 14 or even 16 memmed spells at our disposal?</P><P>Allowing level 60 casters to memorize more spells would go a long ways in achieveing some serious BALANCE instead of cheap parlor tricks like ANCIENT SPELLS.</P><P><BR>Dornette<BR>60 necromancer (retired)<BR>The Nameless<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
