        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> For me the following would be important fixes.</P><P>1) DoT stacking: this is just a most for raiding Necromancers who depend upon DoTs for their damage.  Now if DoT stacking can not be accomplished in the current code then add some new DoTs and a decent non restritive DD spell.  Also keep in mind that VI needs to ensure that mobs have enough "effect slots" to deal with either changes.</P><P>2) Caster Focus items: these where one of the major things I was looking forward to in Luclin and I am pretty disappointed that they never made it into the game.  Finish and implement several different "stages" of focus items, including new Pet focus items.</P><P>3) Fix the current bugs in our spells and make the extremely rare spells a bit more attainable [EoT and non illusion verisons of Ignite/Chill Bones for example].</P><P>4) Re-examine the AA skills: <BR>  *Mass Group Buff: When you consider the only group buff we have is group DMF [which is pretty rare] this ability just does not make any sense.  Look into replacing this will something more usefull.<BR> *Flesh to Bone: Ok, who thought this one up?!?  For the point cost this should like the Mages ability to summon componentless pets<BR> *Dire Charm: Still serious problems with the targeting code.<BR> *Life Burn: Possible stacking issues due to the DoT portition of this ability and it is not able to Crit<BR> *Casting Fury: Does not work with any spell that has a secondary duration effect.  This should be changed, espically considering the secondary effects are non damage related.  It would also be nice to allow DoTs to land critical attacks</P><P>5) Pets: Allowing pets to recieve group buffs would be a great thing.  It would also be nice if our Pet buffs carried a resistance buff bonus.  Pathing still needs to be examined in several zones.</P><P>Bril</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to To