        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> This is basically for all casters in general. Casters are dependent on mana. What I think all casters want is the ability to keep up with the melee in the dmg department and not always go oom. Most want this to be effective at the raid level without adversely creating problems with soloing.  So here is my idea. Doesn’t affect soloing to much, but it makes all casters desired and useful in yet another way at raids and in groups.</P><P>1) Let the wizards familiar buff affect the group. Is it 6 hp tick mana regen? Im not sure.<BR>2) Allow Mages to summon an item that adds +6 mana regen with 2 charges. 20 min duration buff.<BR>3) Level 60 Necro spell of group lich equal to level 49 lich. <BR>4) Allow Clairty to stack with Lich spells.<BR>5) Allow all mana regen spells to stack.<BR>6) Reduce aggro on all spells 50%<BR>7) 51+ Double are mana pools (Wizzies would love that)<BR>8) 51+ Double are normal mana regen rate<BR>9) 51+ regen mana while standing still as if we were sitting</P><P>So with all that and POG you get 46 mana back per tick. That doesn’t include bard song so add like 11 more I believe. With bard song and regen you would never lose hp, actually gaining 1 or 2 per tick. Add in the beastlord buff and it goes to 48 or 49 per tick. Now with the necro in the group mind wracking it goes to an amazing 96 mana per tick regen for 24 seconds. And it only gets better with natural mana regen and FT items.  </P><P><BR> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
